710588f-c.title: Manhattan: 11th Avenue - West Street
710588f-c.text:
11th Avenue, north from its beginning at West and Gansevoort
Streets. In the forecround is the Gansevoort Market Stand. To the
left are the distinctive buildiigs that constitute West Washingt n
Market. Beyond are the Hudson (North) River municipal piers that
line the west side of 11th Avenue. The 11-story utilitarian structure
on the ri,ht is the National Biscuit Company plant. This extends be-
tween 10th and 11th Avenues. Incidentally the latter thoroughfare
begins here; converging with 11th at Delamater Suuare (foot of W. 13th
Street).
April 3, 1929
Views 1,2,3
P. L. Sperr
